<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-28T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="170" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6374/1175: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-28T18:00:00-04:00">June 28, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>81. Referring to my telegram No. 80, June 26, 11 a.m., Minister of
                            Finance informed representative of National City Bank that article 30 of
                            the eighth draft would be eliminated. I had indicated to the Minister
                            for Foreign Affairs that the proposed discrimination against American
                            interests could not be accepted.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
